declarations.comments: Permanently remove a job from a queue. Once you have canceled a job, you can't start it again. You can't delete a running job.
declarations.title: cancelJob

declarations.comments: Create a new transcoding job. For information about jobs and job settings, see the User Guide at http://docs.aws.amazon.com/mediaconvert/latest/ug/what-is.html
declarations.title: createJob

declarations.comments: Create a new job template. For information about job templates see the User Guide at http://docs.aws.amazon.com/mediaconvert/latest/ug/what-is.html
declarations.title: createJobTemplate

declarations.comments: Create a new preset. For information about job templates see the User Guide at http://docs.aws.amazon.com/mediaconvert/latest/ug/what-is.html
declarations.title: createPreset

declarations.comments: Create a new transcoding queue. For information about job templates see the User Guide at http://docs.aws.amazon.com/mediaconvert/latest/ug/what-is.html
declarations.title: createQueue

declarations.comments: Permanently delete a job template you have created.
declarations.title: deleteJobTemplate

declarations.comments: Permanently delete a preset you have created.
declarations.title: deletePreset

declarations.comments: Permanently delete a queue you have created.
declarations.title: deleteQueue

declarations.comments: Send an request with an empty body to the regional API endpoint to get your account API endpoint.
declarations.title: describeEndpoints

declarations.comments: Retrieve the JSON for a specific completed transcoding job.
declarations.title: getJob

declarations.comments: Retrieve the JSON for a specific job template.
declarations.title: getJobTemplate

declarations.comments: Retrieve the JSON for a specific preset.
declarations.title: getPreset

declarations.comments: Retrieve the JSON for a specific queue.
declarations.title: getQueue

declarations.comments: Retrieve a JSON array of up to twenty of your job templates. This will return the templates themselves, not just a list of them. To retrieve the next twenty templates, use the nextToken string returned with the array
declarations.title: listJobTemplates

declarations.comments: Retrieve a JSON array of up to twenty of your most recently created jobs. This array includes in-process, completed, and errored jobs. This will return the jobs themselves, not just a list of the jobs. To retrieve the twenty next most recent jobs, use the nextToken string returned with the array.
declarations.title: listJobs

declarations.comments: Retrieve a JSON array of up to twenty of your presets. This will return the presets themselves, not just a list of them. To retrieve the next twenty presets, use the nextToken string returned with the array.
declarations.title: listPresets

declarations.comments: Retrieve a JSON array of up to twenty of your queues. This will return the queues themselves, not just a list of them. To retrieve the next twenty queues, use the nextToken string returned with the array.
declarations.title: listQueues

declarations.comments: Modify one of your existing job templates.
declarations.title: updateJobTemplate

declarations.comments: Modify one of your existing presets.
declarations.title: updatePreset

declarations.comments: Modify one of your existing queues.
declarations.title: updateQueue

declarations.comments: Choose BROADCASTER_MIXED_AD when the input contains pre-mixed main audio + audio description (AD) as a stereo pair. The value for AudioType will be set to 3, which signals to downstream systems that this stream contains "broadcaster mixed AD". Note that the input received by the encoder must contain pre-mixed audio; the encoder does not perform the mixing. When you choose BROADCASTER_MIXED_AD, the encoder ignores any values you provide in AudioType and  FollowInputAudioType. Choose NORMAL when the input does not contain pre-mixed audio + audio description (AD). In this case, the encoder will use any values you provide for AudioType and FollowInputAudioType.
declarations.title: AacAudioDescriptionBroadcasterMix

declarations.comments: AAC Profile.
declarations.title: AacCodecProfile

declarations.comments: Mono (Audio Description), Mono, Stereo, or 5.1 channel layout. Valid values depend on rate control mode and profile. "1.0 - Audio Description (Receiver Mix)" setting receives a stereo description plus control track and emits a mono AAC encode of the description track, with control data emitted in the PES header as per ETSI TS 101 154 Annex E.
declarations.title: AacCodingMode

declarations.comments: Rate Control Mode.
declarations.title: AacRateControlMode

declarations.comments: Enables LATM/LOAS AAC output. Note that if you use LATM/LOAS AAC in an output, you must choose "No container" for the output container.
declarations.title: AacRawFormat

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Codec) under (AudioDescriptions)>(CodecSettings) to the value AAC.
declarations.title: AacSettings

declarations.comments: Use MPEG-2 AAC instead of MPEG-4 AAC audio for raw or MPEG-2 Transport Stream containers.
declarations.title: AacSpecification

declarations.comments: VBR Quality Level - Only used if rate_control_mode is VBR.
declarations.title: AacVbrQuality

declarations.comments: Specifies the "Bitstream Mode" (bsmod) for the emitted AC-3 stream. See ATSC A/52-2012 for background on these values.
declarations.title: Ac3BitstreamMode

declarations.comments: Dolby Digital coding mode. Determines number of channels.
declarations.title: Ac3CodingMode

declarations.comments: If set to FILM_STANDARD, adds dynamic range compression signaling to the output bitstream as defined in the Dolby Digital specification.
declarations.title: Ac3DynamicRangeCompressionProfile

declarations.comments: Applies a 120Hz lowpass filter to the LFE channel prior to encoding. Only valid with 3_2_LFE coding mode.
declarations.title: Ac3LfeFilter

declarations.comments: When set to FOLLOW_INPUT, encoder metadata will be sourced from the DD, DD+, or DolbyE decoder that supplied this audio data. If audio was not supplied from one of these streams, then the static metadata settings will be used.
declarations.title: Ac3MetadataControl

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Codec) under (AudioDescriptions)>(CodecSettings) to the value AC3.
declarations.title: Ac3Settings

declarations.comments: This setting only applies to H.264 and MPEG2 outputs. Use Insert AFD signaling (AfdSignaling) to whether there are AFD values in the output video data and what those values are. * Choose None to remove all AFD values from this output. * Choose Fixed to ignore input AFD values and instead encode the value specified in the job. * Choose Auto to calculate output AFD values based on the input AFD scaler data.
declarations.title: AfdSignaling

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Codec) under (AudioDescriptions)>(CodecSettings) to the value AIFF.
declarations.title: AiffSettings

declarations.comments: Settings for ancillary captions source.
declarations.title: AncillarySourceSettings

declarations.comments: Enable Anti-alias (AntiAlias) to enhance sharp edges in video output when your input resolution is much larger than your output resolution. Default is enabled.
declarations.title: AntiAlias

declarations.comments: Type of Audio codec.
declarations.title: AudioCodec

declarations.comments: Audio codec settings (CodecSettings) under (AudioDescriptions) contains the group of settings related to audio encoding. The settings in this group vary depending on the value you choose for Audio codec (Codec). For each codec enum you choose, define the corresponding settings object. The following lists the codec enum, settings object pairs. * AAC, AacSettings * MP2, Mp2Settings * WAV, WavSettings * AIFF, AiffSettings * AC3, Ac3Settings * EAC3, Eac3Settings
declarations.title: AudioCodecSettings

declarations.comments: When an "Audio Description":#audio_description specifies an AudioSelector or AudioSelectorGroup  for which no matching source is found in the input, then the audio selector marked as DEFAULT will be used.  If none are marked as default, silence will be inserted for the duration of the input.
declarations.title: AudioDefaultSelection

declarations.comments: Description of audio output
declarations.title: AudioDescription

declarations.comments: Choosing FOLLOW_INPUT will cause the ISO 639 language code of the output to follow the ISO 639 language code of the input. The language specified for languageCode' will be used when USE_CONFIGURED is selected or when FOLLOW_INPUT is selected but there is no ISO 639 language code specified by the input.
declarations.title: AudioLanguageCodeControl

declarations.comments: Audio normalization algorithm to use. 1770-1 conforms to the CALM Act specification, 1770-2 conforms to the EBU R-128 specification.
declarations.title: AudioNormalizationAlgorithm

declarations.comments: When enabled the output audio is corrected using the chosen algorithm. If disabled, the audio will be measured but not adjusted.
declarations.title: AudioNormalizationAlgorithmControl

declarations.comments: If set to LOG, log each output's audio track loudness to a CSV file.
declarations.title: AudioNormalizationLoudnessLogging

declarations.comments: If set to TRUE_PEAK, calculate and log the TruePeak for each output's audio track loudness.
declarations.title: AudioNormalizationPeakCalculation

declarations.comments: Advanced audio normalization settings.
declarations.title: AudioNormalizationSettings

declarations.comments: Selector for Audio
declarations.title: AudioSelector

declarations.comments: Group of Audio Selectors
declarations.title: AudioSelectorGroup

declarations.comments: Specifies the type of the audio selector.
declarations.title: AudioSelectorType

declarations.comments: When set to FOLLOW_INPUT, if the input contains an ISO 639 audio_type, then that value is passed through to the output. If the input contains no ISO 639 audio_type, the value in Audio Type is included in the output. Otherwise the value in Audio Type is included in the output. Note that this field and audioType are both ignored if audioDescriptionBroadcasterMix is set to BROADCASTER_MIXED_AD.
declarations.title: AudioTypeControl

declarations.comments: Settings for Avail Blanking
declarations.title: AvailBlanking

declarations.comments: The service can't process your request because of a problem in the request. Please check your request form and syntax.
declarations.title: BadRequestException

declarations.comments: Burn-In Destination Settings.
declarations.title: BurninDestinationSettings

declarations.comments: If no explicit x_position or y_position is provided, setting alignment to centered will place the captions at the bottom center of the output. Similarly, setting a left alignment will align captions to the bottom left of the output. If x and y positions are given in conjunction with the alignment parameter, the font will be justified (either left or centered) relative to those coordinates. This option is not valid for source captions that are STL, 608/embedded or teletext. These source settings are already pre-defined by the caption stream. All burn-in and DVB-Sub font settings must match.
declarations.title: BurninSubtitleAlignment

declarations.comments:
Specifies the color of the rectangle behind the captions.
All burn-in and DVB-Sub font settings must match.
declarations.title: BurninSubtitleBackgroundColor

declarations.comments: Specifies the color of the burned-in captions. This option is not valid for source captions that are STL, 608/embedded or teletext. These source settings are already pre-defined by the caption stream. All burn-in and DVB-Sub font settings must match.
declarations.title: BurninSubtitleFontColor

declarations.comments: Specifies font outline color. This option is not valid for source captions that are either 608/embedded or teletext. These source settings are already pre-defined by the caption stream. All burn-in and DVB-Sub font settings must match.
declarations.title: BurninSubtitleOutlineColor

declarations.comments:
Specifies the color of the shadow cast by the captions.
All burn-in and DVB-Sub font settings must match.
declarations.title: BurninSubtitleShadowColor

declarations.comments: Controls whether a fixed grid size or proportional font spacing will be used to generate the output subtitles bitmap. Only applicable for Teletext inputs and DVB-Sub/Burn-in outputs.
declarations.title: BurninSubtitleTeletextSpacing

declarations.comments: Description of Caption output
declarations.title: CaptionDescription

declarations.comments: Caption Description for preset
declarations.title: CaptionDescriptionPreset

declarations.comments: Specific settings required by destination type. Note that burnin_destination_settings are not available if the source of the caption data is Embedded or Teletext.
declarations.title: CaptionDestinationSettings

declarations.comments: Type of Caption output, including Burn-In, Embedded, SCC, SRT, TTML, WebVTT, DVB-Sub, Teletext.
declarations.title: CaptionDestinationType

declarations.comments: Caption inputs to be mapped to caption outputs.
declarations.title: CaptionSelector

declarations.comments: Source settings (SourceSettings) contains the group of settings for captions in the input.
declarations.title: CaptionSourceSettings

declarations.comments: Use Source (SourceType) to identify the format of your input captions.  The service cannot auto-detect caption format.
declarations.title: CaptionSourceType

declarations.comments: Channel mapping (ChannelMapping) contains the group of fields that hold the remixing value for each channel. Units are in dB. Acceptable values are within the range from -60 (mute) through 6. A setting of 0 passes the input channel unchanged to the output channel (no attenuation or amplification).
declarations.title: ChannelMapping

declarations.comments: Settings for color correction.
declarations.title: ColorCorrector

declarations.comments: Enable Insert color metadata (ColorMetadata) to include color metadata in this output. This setting is enabled by default.
declarations.title: ColorMetadata

declarations.comments: Specifies the colorspace of an input. This setting works in tandem with "Color Corrector":#color_corrector > color_space_conversion to determine if any conversion will be performed.
declarations.title: ColorSpace

declarations.comments: Determines if colorspace conversion will be performed. If set to _None_, no conversion will be performed. If _Force 601_ or _Force 709_ are selected, conversion will be performed for inputs with differing colorspaces. An input's colorspace can be specified explicitly in the "Video Selector":#inputs-video_selector if necessary.
declarations.title: ColorSpaceConversion

declarations.comments: There are two sources for color metadata, the input file and the job configuration. This enum controls which takes precedence. FORCE: System will use color metadata supplied by user, if any. If the user does not supply color metadata the system will use data from the source. FALLBACK: System will use color metadata from the source. If source has no color metadata, the system will use user-supplied color metadata values if available.
declarations.title: ColorSpaceUsage

declarations.comments: The service could not complete your request because there is a conflict with the current state of the resource.
declarations.title: ConflictException

declarations.comments: Container specific settings.
declarations.title: ContainerSettings

declarations.comments: Container for this output. Some containers require a container settings object. If not specified, the default object will be created.
declarations.title: ContainerType

declarations.comments: Specifies DRM settings for DASH outputs.
declarations.title: DashIsoEncryptionSettings

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Type) under (OutputGroups)>(OutputGroupSettings) to DASH_ISO_GROUP_SETTINGS.
declarations.title: DashIsoGroupSettings

declarations.comments: Supports HbbTV specification as indicated
declarations.title: DashIsoHbbtvCompliance

declarations.comments: When set to SINGLE_FILE, a single output file is generated, which is internally segmented using the Fragment Length and Segment Length. When set to SEGMENTED_FILES, separate segment files will be created.
declarations.title: DashIsoSegmentControl

declarations.comments: Only applies when you set Deinterlacer (DeinterlaceMode) to Deinterlace (DEINTERLACE) or Adaptive (ADAPTIVE). Motion adaptive interpolate (INTERPOLATE) produces sharper pictures, while blend (BLEND) produces smoother motion. Use (INTERPOLATE_TICKER) OR (BLEND_TICKER) if your source file includes a ticker, such as a scrolling headline at the bottom of the frame.
declarations.title: DeinterlaceAlgorithm

declarations.comments: Settings for deinterlacer
declarations.title: Deinterlacer

declarations.comments: - When set to NORMAL (default), the deinterlacer does not convert frames that are tagged  in metadata as progressive. It will only convert those that are tagged as some other type. - When set to FORCE_ALL_FRAMES, the deinterlacer converts every frame to progressive - even those that are already tagged as progressive. Turn Force mode on only if there is  a good chance that the metadata has tagged frames as progressive when they are not  progressive. Do not turn on otherwise; processing frames that are already progressive  into progressive will probably result in lower quality video.
declarations.title: DeinterlacerControl

declarations.comments: Use Deinterlacer (DeinterlaceMode) to choose how the service will do deinterlacing. Default is Deinterlace. - Deinterlace converts interlaced to progressive. - Inverse telecine converts Hard Telecine 29.97i to progressive 23.976p. - Adaptive auto-detects and converts to progressive.
declarations.title: DeinterlacerMode

declarations.comments: DescribeEndpointsRequest
declarations.title: DescribeEndpointsRequest

declarations.comments: Applies only to 29.97 fps outputs. When this feature is enabled, the service will use drop-frame timecode on outputs. If it is not possible to use drop-frame timecode, the system will fall back to non-drop-frame. This setting is enabled by default when Timecode insertion (TimecodeInsertion) is enabled.
declarations.title: DropFrameTimecode

declarations.comments: Inserts DVB Network Information Table (NIT) at the specified table repetition interval.
declarations.title: DvbNitSettings

declarations.comments: Inserts DVB Service Description Table (NIT) at the specified table repetition interval.
declarations.title: DvbSdtSettings

declarations.comments: DVB-Sub Destination Settings
declarations.title: DvbSubDestinationSettings

declarations.comments: DVB Sub Source Settings
declarations.title: DvbSubSourceSettings

declarations.comments: If no explicit x_position or y_position is provided, setting alignment to centered will place the captions at the bottom center of the output. Similarly, setting a left alignment will align captions to the bottom left of the output. If x and y positions are given in conjunction with the alignment parameter, the font will be justified (either left or centered) relative to those coordinates. This option is not valid for source captions that are STL, 608/embedded or teletext. These source settings are already pre-defined by the caption stream. All burn-in and DVB-Sub font settings must match.
declarations.title: DvbSubtitleAlignment

declarations.comments:
Specifies the color of the rectangle behind the captions.
All burn-in and DVB-Sub font settings must match.
declarations.title: DvbSubtitleBackgroundColor

declarations.comments: Specifies the color of the burned-in captions. This option is not valid for source captions that are STL, 608/embedded or teletext. These source settings are already pre-defined by the caption stream. All burn-in and DVB-Sub font settings must match.
declarations.title: DvbSubtitleFontColor

declarations.comments: Specifies font outline color. This option is not valid for source captions that are either 608/embedded or teletext. These source settings are already pre-defined by the caption stream. All burn-in and DVB-Sub font settings must match.
declarations.title: DvbSubtitleOutlineColor

declarations.comments:
Specifies the color of the shadow cast by the captions.
All burn-in and DVB-Sub font settings must match.
declarations.title: DvbSubtitleShadowColor

declarations.comments: Controls whether a fixed grid size or proportional font spacing will be used to generate the output subtitles bitmap. Only applicable for Teletext inputs and DVB-Sub/Burn-in outputs.
declarations.title: DvbSubtitleTeletextSpacing

declarations.comments: Inserts DVB Time and Date Table (TDT) at the specified table repetition interval.
declarations.title: DvbTdtSettings

declarations.comments: If set to ATTENUATE_3_DB, applies a 3 dB attenuation to the surround channels. Only used for 3/2 coding mode.
declarations.title: Eac3AttenuationControl

declarations.comments: Specifies the "Bitstream Mode" (bsmod) for the emitted E-AC-3 stream. See ATSC A/52-2012 (Annex E) for background on these values.
declarations.title: Eac3BitstreamMode

declarations.comments: Dolby Digital Plus coding mode. Determines number of channels.
declarations.title: Eac3CodingMode

declarations.comments: Activates a DC highpass filter for all input channels.
declarations.title: Eac3DcFilter

declarations.comments: Enables Dynamic Range Compression that restricts the absolute peak level for a signal.
declarations.title: Eac3DynamicRangeCompressionLine

declarations.comments: Enables Heavy Dynamic Range Compression, ensures that the instantaneous signal peaks do not exceed specified levels.
declarations.title: Eac3DynamicRangeCompressionRf

declarations.comments: When encoding 3/2 audio, controls whether the LFE channel is enabled
declarations.title: Eac3LfeControl

declarations.comments: Applies a 120Hz lowpass filter to the LFE channel prior to encoding. Only valid with 3_2_LFE coding mode.
declarations.title: Eac3LfeFilter

declarations.comments: When set to FOLLOW_INPUT, encoder metadata will be sourced from the DD, DD+, or DolbyE decoder that supplied this audio data. If audio was not supplied from one of these streams, then the static metadata settings will be used.
declarations.title: Eac3MetadataControl

declarations.comments: When set to WHEN_POSSIBLE, input DD+ audio will be passed through if it is present on the input. this detection is dynamic over the life of the transcode. Inputs that alternate between DD+ and non-DD+ content will have a consistent DD+ output as the system alternates between passthrough and encoding.
declarations.title: Eac3PassthroughControl

declarations.comments: Controls the amount of phase-shift applied to the surround channels. Only used for 3/2 coding mode.
declarations.title: Eac3PhaseControl

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Codec) under (AudioDescriptions)>(CodecSettings) to the value EAC3.
declarations.title: Eac3Settings

declarations.comments: Stereo downmix preference. Only used for 3/2 coding mode.
declarations.title: Eac3StereoDownmix

declarations.comments: When encoding 3/2 audio, sets whether an extra center back surround channel is matrix encoded into the left and right surround channels.
declarations.title: Eac3SurroundExMode

declarations.comments: When encoding 2/0 audio, sets whether Dolby Surround is matrix encoded into the two channels.
declarations.title: Eac3SurroundMode

declarations.comments: When set to UPCONVERT, 608 data is both passed through via the "608 compatibility bytes" fields of the 708 wrapper as well as translated into 708. 708 data present in the source content will be discarded.
declarations.title: EmbeddedConvert608To708

declarations.comments: Settings for embedded captions Source
declarations.title: EmbeddedSourceSettings

declarations.comments: Describes account specific API endpoint
declarations.title: Endpoint

declarations.comments: If set to PROGRESSIVE_DOWNLOAD, the MOOV atom is relocated to the beginning of the archive as required for progressive downloading. Otherwise it is placed normally at the end.
declarations.title: F4vMoovPlacement

declarations.comments: Settings for F4v container
declarations.title: F4vSettings

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Type) under (OutputGroups)>(OutputGroupSettings) to FILE_GROUP_SETTINGS.
declarations.title: FileGroupSettings

declarations.comments: If set to UPCONVERT, 608 caption data is both passed through via the "608 compatibility bytes" fields of the 708 wrapper as well as translated into 708. 708 data present in the source content will be discarded.
declarations.title: FileSourceConvert608To708

declarations.comments: Settings for File-based Captions in Source
declarations.title: FileSourceSettings

declarations.comments: You don't have permissions for this action with the credentials you sent.
declarations.title: ForbiddenException

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Codec) under (VideoDescription)>(CodecSettings) to the value FRAME_CAPTURE.
declarations.title: FrameCaptureSettings

declarations.comments: Adaptive quantization. Allows intra-frame quantizers to vary to improve visual quality.
declarations.title: H264AdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: H.264 Level.
declarations.title: H264CodecLevel

declarations.comments: H.264 Profile. High 4:2:2 and 10-bit profiles are only available with the AVC-I License.
declarations.title: H264CodecProfile

declarations.comments: Entropy encoding mode. Use CABAC (must be in Main or High profile) or CAVLC.
declarations.title: H264EntropyEncoding

declarations.comments: Choosing FORCE_FIELD disables PAFF encoding for interlaced outputs.
declarations.title: H264FieldEncoding

declarations.comments: Adjust quantization within each frame to reduce flicker or 'pop' on I-frames.
declarations.title: H264FlickerAdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: Using the API, set FramerateControl to INITIALIZE_FROM_SOURCE if you want the service to use the framerate from the input. Using the console, do this by choosing INITIALIZE_FROM_SOURCE for Framerate.
declarations.title: H264FramerateControl

declarations.comments: When set to INTERPOLATE, produces smoother motion during framerate conversion.
declarations.title: H264FramerateConversionAlgorithm

declarations.comments: If enable, use reference B frames for GOP structures that have B frames > 1.
declarations.title: H264GopBReference

declarations.comments: Indicates if the GOP Size in H264 is specified in frames or seconds. If seconds the system will convert the GOP Size into a frame count at run time.
declarations.title: H264GopSizeUnits

declarations.comments: Use Interlace mode (InterlaceMode) to choose the scan line type for the output. * Top Field First (TOP_FIELD) and Bottom Field First (BOTTOM_FIELD) produce interlaced output with the entire output having the same field polarity (top or bottom first). * Follow, Default Top (FOLLOw_TOP_FIELD) and Follow, Default Bottom (FOLLOW_BOTTOM_FIELD) use the same  field polarity as the source. Therefore, behavior depends on the input scan type. - If the source is interlaced, the output will be interlaced with the same polarity as the source (it will follow the source). The output could therefore be a mix of "top field first" and "bottom field first". - If the source is progressive, the output will be interlaced with "top field first" or "bottom field first" polarity, depending on which of the Follow options you chose.
declarations.title: H264InterlaceMode

declarations.comments: Using the API, enable ParFollowSource if you want the service to use the pixel aspect ratio from the input. Using the console, do this by choosing Follow source for Pixel aspect ratio.
declarations.title: H264ParControl

declarations.comments: Use Quality tuning level (H264QualityTuningLevel) to specifiy whether to use fast single-pass, high-quality singlepass, or high-quality multipass video encoding.
declarations.title: H264QualityTuningLevel

declarations.comments: Rate control mode. CQ uses constant quantizer (qp), ABR (average bitrate) does not write HRD parameters.
declarations.title: H264RateControlMode

declarations.comments: Places a PPS header on each encoded picture, even if repeated.
declarations.title: H264RepeatPps

declarations.comments: Scene change detection (inserts I-frames on scene changes).
declarations.title: H264SceneChangeDetect

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Codec) under (VideoDescription)>(CodecSettings) to the value H_264.
declarations.title: H264Settings

declarations.comments: Enables Slow PAL rate conversion. 23.976fps and 24fps input is relabeled as 25fps, and audio is sped up correspondingly.
declarations.title: H264SlowPal

declarations.comments: Adjust quantization within each frame based on spatial variation of content complexity.
declarations.title: H264SpatialAdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: Produces a bitstream compliant with SMPTE RP-2027.
declarations.title: H264Syntax

declarations.comments: This field applies only if the Streams > Advanced > Framerate (framerate) field  is set to 29.970. This field works with the Streams > Advanced > Preprocessors > Deinterlacer  field (deinterlace_mode) and the Streams > Advanced > Interlaced Mode field (interlace_mode)  to identify the scan type for the output: Progressive, Interlaced, Hard Telecine or Soft Telecine. - Hard: produces 29.97i output from 23.976 input. - Soft: produces 23.976; the player converts this output to 29.97i.
declarations.title: H264Telecine

declarations.comments: Adjust quantization within each frame based on temporal variation of content complexity.
declarations.title: H264TemporalAdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: Inserts timecode for each frame as 4 bytes of an unregistered SEI message.
declarations.title: H264UnregisteredSeiTimecode

declarations.comments: Adaptive quantization. Allows intra-frame quantizers to vary to improve visual quality.
declarations.title: H265AdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: Enables Alternate Transfer Function SEI message for outputs using Hybrid Log Gamma (HLG) Electro-Optical Transfer Function (EOTF).
declarations.title: H265AlternateTransferFunctionSei

declarations.comments: H.265 Level.
declarations.title: H265CodecLevel

declarations.comments: Represents the Profile and Tier, per the HEVC (H.265) specification. Selections are grouped as [Profile] / [Tier], so "Main/High" represents Main Profile with High Tier. 4:2:2 profiles are only available with the HEVC 4:2:2 License.
declarations.title: H265CodecProfile

declarations.comments: Adjust quantization within each frame to reduce flicker or 'pop' on I-frames.
declarations.title: H265FlickerAdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: Using the API, set FramerateControl to INITIALIZE_FROM_SOURCE if you want the service to use the framerate from the input. Using the console, do this by choosing INITIALIZE_FROM_SOURCE for Framerate.
declarations.title: H265FramerateControl

declarations.comments: When set to INTERPOLATE, produces smoother motion during framerate conversion.
declarations.title: H265FramerateConversionAlgorithm

declarations.comments: If enable, use reference B frames for GOP structures that have B frames > 1.
declarations.title: H265GopBReference

declarations.comments: Indicates if the GOP Size in H265 is specified in frames or seconds. If seconds the system will convert the GOP Size into a frame count at run time.
declarations.title: H265GopSizeUnits

declarations.comments: Use Interlace mode (InterlaceMode) to choose the scan line type for the output. * Top Field First (TOP_FIELD) and Bottom Field First (BOTTOM_FIELD) produce interlaced output with the entire output having the same field polarity (top or bottom first). * Follow, Default Top (FOLLOw_TOP_FIELD) and Follow, Default Bottom (FOLLOW_BOTTOM_FIELD) use the same  field polarity as the source. Therefore, behavior depends on the input scan type. - If the source is interlaced, the output will be interlaced with the same polarity as the source (it will follow the source). The output could therefore be a mix of "top field first" and "bottom field first". - If the source is progressive, the output will be interlaced with "top field first" or "bottom field first" polarity, depending on which of the Follow options you chose.
declarations.title: H265InterlaceMode

declarations.comments: Using the API, enable ParFollowSource if you want the service to use the pixel aspect ratio from the input. Using the console, do this by choosing Follow source for Pixel aspect ratio.
declarations.title: H265ParControl

declarations.comments: Use Quality tuning level (H265QualityTuningLevel) to specifiy whether to use fast single-pass, high-quality singlepass, or high-quality multipass video encoding.
declarations.title: H265QualityTuningLevel

declarations.comments: Rate control mode. CQ uses constant quantizer (qp), ABR (average bitrate) does not write HRD parameters.
declarations.title: H265RateControlMode

declarations.comments: Specify Sample Adaptive Offset (SAO) filter strength.  Adaptive mode dynamically selects best strength based on content
declarations.title: H265SampleAdaptiveOffsetFilterMode

declarations.comments: Scene change detection (inserts I-frames on scene changes).
declarations.title: H265SceneChangeDetect

declarations.comments: Settings for H265 codec
declarations.title: H265Settings

declarations.comments: Enables Slow PAL rate conversion. 23.976fps and 24fps input is relabeled as 25fps, and audio is sped up correspondingly.
declarations.title: H265SlowPal

declarations.comments: Adjust quantization within each frame based on spatial variation of content complexity.
declarations.title: H265SpatialAdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: This field applies only if the Streams > Advanced > Framerate (framerate) field  is set to 29.970. This field works with the Streams > Advanced > Preprocessors > Deinterlacer  field (deinterlace_mode) and the Streams > Advanced > Interlaced Mode field (interlace_mode)  to identify the scan type for the output: Progressive, Interlaced, Hard Telecine or Soft Telecine. - Hard: produces 29.97i output from 23.976 input. - Soft: produces 23.976; the player converts this output to 29.97i.
declarations.title: H265Telecine

declarations.comments: Adjust quantization within each frame based on temporal variation of content complexity.
declarations.title: H265TemporalAdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: Enables temporal layer identifiers in the encoded bitstream. Up to 3 layers are supported depending on GOP structure: I- and P-frames form one layer, reference B-frames can form a second layer and non-reference b-frames can form a third layer. Decoders can optionally decode only the lower temporal layers to generate a lower frame rate output. For example, given a bitstream with temporal IDs and with b-frames = 1 (i.e. IbPbPb display order), a decoder could decode all the frames for full frame rate output or only the I and P frames (lowest temporal layer) for a half frame rate output.
declarations.title: H265TemporalIds

declarations.comments: Enable use of tiles, allowing horizontal as well as vertical subdivision of the encoded pictures.
declarations.title: H265Tiles

declarations.comments: Inserts timecode for each frame as 4 bytes of an unregistered SEI message.
declarations.title: H265UnregisteredSeiTimecode

declarations.comments: Use the HDR master display (Hdr10Metadata) settings to provide values for HDR color. These values vary depending on the input video and must be provided by a color grader. Range is 0 to 50,000, each increment represents 0.00002 in CIE1931 color coordinate.
declarations.title: Hdr10Metadata

declarations.comments: Four types of audio-only tracks are supported: Audio-Only Variant Stream The client can play back this audio-only stream instead of video in low-bandwidth scenarios. Represented as an EXT-X-STREAM-INF in the HLS manifest. Alternate Audio, Auto Select, Default Alternate rendition that the client should try to play back by default. Represented as an EXT-X-MEDIA in the HLS manifest with DEFAULT=YES, AUTOSELECT=YES Alternate Audio, Auto Select, Not Default Alternate rendition that the client may try to play back by default. Represented as an EXT-X-MEDIA in the HLS manifest with DEFAULT=NO, AUTOSELECT=YES Alternate Audio, not Auto Select Alternate rendition that the client will not try to play back by default. Represented as an EXT-X-MEDIA in the HLS manifest with DEFAULT=NO, AUTOSELECT=NO
declarations.title: HlsAudioTrackType

declarations.comments: Caption Language Mapping
declarations.title: HlsCaptionLanguageMapping

declarations.comments: Applies only to 608 Embedded output captions. Insert: Include CLOSED-CAPTIONS lines in the manifest. Specify at least one language in the CC1 Language Code field. One CLOSED-CAPTION line is added for each Language Code you specify. Make sure to specify the languages in the order in which they appear in the original source (if the source is embedded format) or the order of the caption selectors (if the source is other than embedded). Otherwise, languages in the manifest will not match up properly with the output captions. None: Include CLOSED-CAPTIONS=NONE line in the manifest. Omit: Omit any CLOSED-CAPTIONS line from the manifest.
declarations.title: HlsCaptionLanguageSetting

declarations.comments: When set to ENABLED, sets #EXT-X-ALLOW-CACHE:no tag, which prevents client from saving media segments for later replay.
declarations.title: HlsClientCache

declarations.comments: Specification to use (RFC-6381 or the default RFC-4281) during m3u8 playlist generation.
declarations.title: HlsCodecSpecification

declarations.comments: Indicates whether segments should be placed in subdirectories.
declarations.title: HlsDirectoryStructure

declarations.comments: Settings for HLS encryption
declarations.title: HlsEncryptionSettings

declarations.comments: Encrypts the segments with the given encryption scheme. Leave blank to disable. Selecting 'Disabled' in the web interface also disables encryption.
declarations.title: HlsEncryptionType

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Type) under (OutputGroups)>(OutputGroupSettings) to HLS_GROUP_SETTINGS.
declarations.title: HlsGroupSettings

declarations.comments: When set to INCLUDE, writes I-Frame Only Manifest in addition to the HLS manifest
declarations.title: HlsIFrameOnlyManifest

declarations.comments: The Initialization Vector is a 128-bit number used in conjunction with the key for encrypting blocks. If set to INCLUDE, Initialization Vector is listed in the manifest. Otherwise Initialization Vector is not in the manifest.
declarations.title: HlsInitializationVectorInManifest

declarations.comments: Indicates which type of key provider is used for encryption.
declarations.title: HlsKeyProviderType

declarations.comments: When set to GZIP, compresses HLS playlist.
declarations.title: HlsManifestCompression

declarations.comments: Indicates whether the output manifest should use floating point values for segment duration.
declarations.title: HlsManifestDurationFormat

declarations.comments: Indicates whether the .m3u8 manifest file should be generated for this HLS output group.
declarations.title: HlsOutputSelection

declarations.comments: Includes or excludes EXT-X-PROGRAM-DATE-TIME tag in .m3u8 manifest files. The value is calculated as follows: either the program date and time are initialized using the input timecode source, or the time is initialized using the input timecode source and the date is initialized using the timestamp_offset.
declarations.title: HlsProgramDateTime

declarations.comments: When set to SINGLE_FILE, emits program as a single media resource (.ts) file, uses #EXT-X-BYTERANGE tags to index segment for playback.
declarations.title: HlsSegmentControl

declarations.comments: Settings for HLS output groups
declarations.title: HlsSettings

declarations.comments: Include or exclude RESOLUTION attribute for video in EXT-X-STREAM-INF tag of variant manifest.
declarations.title: HlsStreamInfResolution

declarations.comments: Indicates ID3 frame that has the timecode.
declarations.title: HlsTimedMetadataId3Frame

declarations.comments: To insert ID3 tags in your output, specify two values. Use ID3 tag (Id3) to specify the base 64 encoded string and use Timecode (TimeCode) to specify the time when the tag should be inserted. To insert multiple ID3 tags in your output, create mulitple instances of ID3 insertion (Id3Insertion).
declarations.title: Id3Insertion

declarations.comments: Enable the Image inserter (ImageInserter) feature to include a graphic overlay on your video. Enable or disable this feature for each output individually. This setting is disabled by default.
declarations.title: ImageInserter

declarations.comments: Specifies media input
declarations.title: Input

declarations.comments: Include one instance of (InputClipping) for each input clip.
declarations.title: InputClipping

declarations.comments: Enable Deblock (InputDeblockFilter) to produce smoother motion in the output. Default is disabled. Only manaully controllable for MPEG2 and uncompressed video inputs.
declarations.title: InputDeblockFilter

declarations.comments: Enable Denoise (InputDenoiseFilter) to filter noise from the input.  Default is disabled. Only applicable to MPEG2, H.264, H.265, and uncompressed video inputs.
declarations.title: InputDenoiseFilter

declarations.comments: Use Filter enable (InputFilterEnable) to specify how the transcoding service applies the denoise and deblock filters. You must also enable the filters separately, with Denoise (InputDenoiseFilter) and Deblock (InputDeblockFilter). * Auto - The transcoding service determines whether to apply filtering, depending on input type and quality. * Disable - The input is not filtered. This is true even if you use the API to enable them in (InputDeblockFilter) and (InputDeblockFilter). * Force - The in put is filtered regardless of input type.
declarations.title: InputFilterEnable

declarations.comments: Set PSI control (InputPsiControl) for transport stream inputs to specify which data the demux process to scans. * Ignore PSI - Scan all PIDs for audio and video. * Use PSI - Scan only PSI data.
declarations.title: InputPsiControl

declarations.comments: Specified video input in a template.
declarations.title: InputTemplate

declarations.comments: Use Timecode source (InputTimecodeSource) to specify how timecode information from your input is adjusted and encoded in all outputs for the job. Default is embedded. Set to Embedded (EMBEDDED) to use the timecode that is in the input video. If no embedded timecode is in the source, will set the timecode for the first frame to 00:00:00:00. Set to Start at 0 (ZEROBASED) to set the timecode of the initial frame to 00:00:00:00. Set to Specified start (SPECIFIEDSTART) to provide the initial timecode yourself the setting (Start).
declarations.title: InputTimecodeSource

declarations.comments: Settings for Insertable Image
declarations.title: InsertableImage

declarations.comments: The service encountered an unexpected condition and cannot fulfill your request.
declarations.title: InternalServerErrorException

declarations.comments: Each job converts an input file into an output file or files. For more information, see the User Guide at http://docs.aws.amazon.com/mediaconvert/latest/ug/what-is.html
declarations.title: Job

declarations.comments: JobSettings contains all the transcode settings for a job.
declarations.title: JobSettings

declarations.comments: A job's status can be SUBMITTED, PROGRESSING, COMPLETE, CANCELED, or ERROR.
declarations.title: JobStatus

declarations.comments: A job template is a pre-made set of encoding instructions that you can use to quickly create a job.
declarations.title: JobTemplate

declarations.comments: Optional. When you request a list of job templates, you can choose to list them alphabetically by NAME or chronologically by CREATION_DATE. If you don't specify, the service will list them by name.
declarations.title: JobTemplateListBy

declarations.comments: JobTemplateSettings contains all the transcode settings saved in the template that will be applied to jobs created from it.
declarations.title: JobTemplateSettings

declarations.comments: Code to specify the language, following the specification "ISO 639-2 three-digit code":http://www.loc.gov/standards/iso639-2/
declarations.title: LanguageCode

declarations.comments: Selects between the DVB and ATSC buffer models for Dolby Digital audio.
declarations.title: M2tsAudioBufferModel

declarations.comments: Controls what buffer model to use for accurate interleaving. If set to MULTIPLEX, use multiplex  buffer model. If set to NONE, this can lead to lower latency, but low-memory devices may not be able to play back the stream without interruptions.
declarations.title: M2tsBufferModel

declarations.comments: When set to VIDEO_AND_FIXED_INTERVALS, audio EBP markers will be added to partitions 3 and 4. The interval between these additional markers will be fixed, and will be slightly shorter than the video EBP marker interval. When set to VIDEO_INTERVAL, these additional markers will not be inserted. Only applicable when EBP segmentation markers are is selected (segmentationMarkers is EBP or EBP_LEGACY).
declarations.title: M2tsEbpAudioInterval

declarations.comments: Selects which PIDs to place EBP markers on. They can either be placed only on the video PID, or on both the video PID and all audio PIDs. Only applicable when EBP segmentation markers are is selected (segmentationMarkers is EBP or EBP_LEGACY).
declarations.title: M2tsEbpPlacement

declarations.comments: Controls whether to include the ES Rate field in the PES header.
declarations.title: M2tsEsRateInPes

declarations.comments: If INSERT, Nielsen inaudible tones for media tracking will be detected in the input audio and an equivalent ID3 tag will be inserted in the output.
declarations.title: M2tsNielsenId3

declarations.comments: When set to PCR_EVERY_PES_PACKET, a Program Clock Reference value is inserted for every Packetized Elementary Stream (PES) header. This is effective only when the PCR PID is the same as the video or audio elementary stream.
declarations.title: M2tsPcrControl

declarations.comments: When set to CBR, inserts null packets into transport stream to fill specified bitrate. When set to VBR, the bitrate setting acts as the maximum bitrate, but the output will not be padded up to that bitrate.
declarations.title: M2tsRateMode

declarations.comments: Enables SCTE-35 passthrough (scte35Source) to pass any SCTE-35 signals from input to output.
declarations.title: M2tsScte35Source

declarations.comments: Inserts segmentation markers at each segmentation_time period. rai_segstart sets the Random Access Indicator bit in the adaptation field. rai_adapt sets the RAI bit and adds the current timecode in the private data bytes. psi_segstart inserts PAT and PMT tables at the start of segments. ebp adds Encoder Boundary Point information to the adaptation field as per OpenCable specification OC-SP-EBP-I01-130118. ebp_legacy adds Encoder Boundary Point information to the adaptation field using a legacy proprietary format.
declarations.title: M2tsSegmentationMarkers

declarations.comments: The segmentation style parameter controls how segmentation markers are inserted into the transport stream. With avails, it is possible that segments may be truncated, which can influence where future segmentation markers are inserted. When a segmentation style of "reset_cadence" is selected and a segment is truncated due to an avail, we will reset the segmentation cadence. This means the subsequent segment will have a duration of of $segmentation_time seconds. When a segmentation style of "maintain_cadence" is selected and a segment is truncated due to an avail, we will not reset the segmentation cadence. This means the subsequent segment will likely be truncated as well. However, all segments after that will have a duration of $segmentation_time seconds. Note that EBP lookahead is a slight exception to this rule.
declarations.title: M2tsSegmentationStyle

declarations.comments: Settings for M2TS Container.
declarations.title: M2tsSettings

declarations.comments: If INSERT, Nielsen inaudible tones for media tracking will be detected in the input audio and an equivalent ID3 tag will be inserted in the output.
declarations.title: M3u8NielsenId3

declarations.comments: When set to PCR_EVERY_PES_PACKET a Program Clock Reference value is inserted for every Packetized Elementary Stream (PES) header. This parameter is effective only when the PCR PID is the same as the video or audio elementary stream.
declarations.title: M3u8PcrControl

declarations.comments: Enables SCTE-35 passthrough (scte35Source) to pass any SCTE-35 signals from input to output.
declarations.title: M3u8Scte35Source

declarations.comments: Settings for TS segments in HLS
declarations.title: M3u8Settings

declarations.comments: When enabled, include 'clap' atom if appropriate for the video output settings.
declarations.title: MovClapAtom

declarations.comments: When enabled, file composition times will start at zero, composition times in the 'ctts' (composition time to sample) box for B-frames will be negative, and a 'cslg' (composition shift least greatest) box will be included per 14496-1 amendment 1. This improves compatibility with Apple players and tools.
declarations.title: MovCslgAtom

declarations.comments: When set to XDCAM, writes MPEG2 video streams into the QuickTime file using XDCAM fourcc codes. This increases compatibility with Apple editors and players, but may decrease compatibility with other players. Only applicable when the video codec is MPEG2.
declarations.title: MovMpeg2FourCCControl

declarations.comments: If set to OMNEON, inserts Omneon-compatible padding
declarations.title: MovPaddingControl

declarations.comments: A value of 'external' creates separate media files and the wrapper file (.mov) contains references to these media files. A value of 'self_contained' creates only a wrapper (.mov) file and this file contains all of the media.
declarations.title: MovReference

declarations.comments: Settings for MOV Container.
declarations.title: MovSettings

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Codec) under (AudioDescriptions)>(CodecSettings) to the value MP2.
declarations.title: Mp2Settings

declarations.comments: When enabled, file composition times will start at zero, composition times in the 'ctts' (composition time to sample) box for B-frames will be negative, and a 'cslg' (composition shift least greatest) box will be included per 14496-1 amendment 1. This improves compatibility with Apple players and tools.
declarations.title: Mp4CslgAtom

declarations.comments: Inserts a free-space box immediately after the moov box.
declarations.title: Mp4FreeSpaceBox

declarations.comments: If set to PROGRESSIVE_DOWNLOAD, the MOOV atom is relocated to the beginning of the archive as required for progressive downloading. Otherwise it is placed normally at the end.
declarations.title: Mp4MoovPlacement

declarations.comments: Settings for MP4 Container
declarations.title: Mp4Settings

declarations.comments: Adaptive quantization. Allows intra-frame quantizers to vary to improve visual quality.
declarations.title: Mpeg2AdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: Use Level (Mpeg2CodecLevel) to set the MPEG-2 level for the video output.
declarations.title: Mpeg2CodecLevel

declarations.comments: Use Profile (Mpeg2CodecProfile) to set the MPEG-2 profile for the video output.
declarations.title: Mpeg2CodecProfile

declarations.comments: Using the API, set FramerateControl to INITIALIZE_FROM_SOURCE if you want the service to use the framerate from the input. Using the console, do this by choosing INITIALIZE_FROM_SOURCE for Framerate.
declarations.title: Mpeg2FramerateControl

declarations.comments: When set to INTERPOLATE, produces smoother motion during framerate conversion.
declarations.title: Mpeg2FramerateConversionAlgorithm

declarations.comments: Indicates if the GOP Size in MPEG2 is specified in frames or seconds. If seconds the system will convert the GOP Size into a frame count at run time.
declarations.title: Mpeg2GopSizeUnits

declarations.comments: Use Interlace mode (InterlaceMode) to choose the scan line type for the output. * Top Field First (TOP_FIELD) and Bottom Field First (BOTTOM_FIELD) produce interlaced output with the entire output having the same field polarity (top or bottom first). * Follow, Default Top (FOLLOw_TOP_FIELD) and Follow, Default Bottom (FOLLOW_BOTTOM_FIELD) use the same  field polarity as the source. Therefore, behavior depends on the input scan type. - If the source is interlaced, the output will be interlaced with the same polarity as the source (it will follow the source). The output could therefore be a mix of "top field first" and "bottom field first". - If the source is progressive, the output will be interlaced with "top field first" or "bottom field first" polarity, depending on which of the Follow options you chose.

declarations.comments: Use Intra DC precision (Mpeg2IntraDcPrecision) to set quantization precision for intra-block DC coefficients. If you choose the value auto, the service will automatically select the precision based on the per-frame compression ratio.
declarations.title: Mpeg2IntraDcPrecision

declarations.comments: Using the API, enable ParFollowSource if you want the service to use the pixel aspect ratio from the input. Using the console, do this by choosing Follow source for Pixel aspect ratio.
declarations.title: Mpeg2ParControl

declarations.comments: Use Quality tuning level (Mpeg2QualityTuningLevel) to specifiy whether to use single-pass or multipass video encoding.
declarations.title: Mpeg2QualityTuningLevel

declarations.comments: Use Rate control mode (Mpeg2RateControlMode) to specifiy whether the bitrate is variable (vbr) or constant (cbr).
declarations.title: Mpeg2RateControlMode

declarations.comments: Scene change detection (inserts I-frames on scene changes).
declarations.title: Mpeg2SceneChangeDetect

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Codec) under (VideoDescription)>(CodecSettings) to the value MPEG2.
declarations.title: Mpeg2Settings

declarations.comments: Enables Slow PAL rate conversion. 23.976fps and 24fps input is relabeled as 25fps, and audio is sped up correspondingly.
declarations.title: Mpeg2SlowPal

declarations.comments: Adjust quantization within each frame based on spatial variation of content complexity.
declarations.title: Mpeg2SpatialAdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: Produces a Type D-10 compatible bitstream (SMPTE 356M-2001).
declarations.title: Mpeg2Syntax

declarations.comments: Only use Telecine (Mpeg2Telecine) when you set Framerate (Framerate) to 29.970. Set Telecine (Mpeg2Telecine) to Hard (hard) to produce a 29.97i output from a 23.976 input. Set it to Soft (soft) to produce 23.976 output and leave converstion to the player.
declarations.title: Mpeg2Telecine

declarations.comments: Adjust quantization within each frame based on temporal variation of content complexity.
declarations.title: Mpeg2TemporalAdaptiveQuantization

declarations.comments: COMBINE_DUPLICATE_STREAMS combines identical audio encoding settings across a Microsoft Smooth output group into a single audio stream.
declarations.title: MsSmoothAudioDeduplication

declarations.comments: If you are using DRM, set DRM System (MsSmoothEncryptionSettings) to specify the value SpekeKeyProvider.
declarations.title: MsSmoothEncryptionSettings

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Type) under (OutputGroups)>(OutputGroupSettings) to MS_SMOOTH_GROUP_SETTINGS.
declarations.title: MsSmoothGroupSettings

declarations.comments: Use Manifest encoding (MsSmoothManifestEncoding) to specify the encoding format for the server and client manifest. Valid options are utf8 and utf16.

declarations.title: NielsenConfiguration

declarations.comments: Enable the Noise reducer (NoiseReducer) feature to remove noise from your video output if necessary. Enable or disable this feature for each output individually. This setting is disabled by default. When you enable Noise reducer (NoiseReducer), you must also select a value for Noise reducer filter (NoiseReducerFilter).
declarations.title: NoiseReducer

declarations.comments: Use Noise reducer filter (NoiseReducerFilter) to select one of the following spatial image filtering functions. To use this setting, you must also enable Noise reducer (NoiseReducer). * Bilateral is an edge preserving noise reduction filter * Mean (softest), Gaussian, Lanczos, and Sharpen (sharpest) are convolution filters * Conserve is a min/max noise reduction filter * Spatial is frequency-domain filter based on JND principles.
declarations.title: NoiseReducerFilter

declarations.comments: Settings for a noise reducer filter
declarations.title: NoiseReducerFilterSettings

declarations.comments: Noise reducer filter settings for spatial filter.

declarations.comments: When set to INTERPOLATE, produces smoother motion during framerate conversion.

declarations.comments: Use Interlace mode (InterlaceMode) to choose the scan line type for the output. * Top Field First (TOP_FIELD) and Bottom Field First (BOTTOM_FIELD) produce interlaced output with the entire output having the same field polarity (top or bottom first). * Follow, Default Top (FOLLOw_TOP_FIELD) and Follow, Default Bottom (FOLLOW_BOTTOM_FIELD) use the same  field polarity as the source. Therefore, behavior depends on the input scan type. - If the source is interlaced, the output will be interlaced with the same polarity as the source (it will follow the source). The output could therefore be a mix of "top field first" and "bottom field first". - If the source is progressive, the output will be interlaced with "top field first" or "bottom field first" polarity, depending on which of the Follow options you chose.

Set to Follow source (INITIALIZE_FROM_SOURCE) to use the pixel aspect ratio from the input.  To specify a different pixel aspect ratio: Using the console, choose it from the dropdown menu. Using the API, set ProresParControl to (SPECIFIED) and provide  for (ParNumerator) and (ParDenominator).
declarations.title: ProresParControl

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Codec) under (VideoDescription)>(CodecSettings) to the value PRORES.
declarations.title: ProresSettings

declarations.comments: Enables Slow PAL rate conversion. 23.976fps and 24fps input is relabeled as 25fps, and audio is sped up correspondingly.
declarations.title: ProresSlowPal

declarations.comments: Only use Telecine (ProresTelecine) when you set Framerate (Framerate) to 29.970. Set Telecine (ProresTelecine) to Hard (hard) to produce a 29.97i output from a 23.976 input. Set it to Soft (soft) to produce 23.976 output and leave converstion to the player.
declarations.title: ProresTelecine

declarations.comments: MediaConvert jobs are submitted to a queue. Unless specified otherwise jobs are submitted to a built-in default queue. User can create additional queues to separate the jobs of different categories or priority.
declarations.title: Queue

declarations.comments: Optional. When you request a list of queues, you can choose to list them alphabetically by NAME or chronologically by CREATION_DATE. If you don't specify, the service will list them by creation date.
declarations.title: QueueListBy

declarations.comments: Queues can be ACTIVE or PAUSED. If you pause a queue, jobs in that queue will not begin. Jobs running when a queue is paused continue to run until they finish or error out.
declarations.title: QueueStatus

declarations.comments: Use Rectangle to identify a specific area of the video frame.
declarations.title: Rectangle

declarations.comments: Use Manual audio remixing (RemixSettings) to adjust audio levels for each output channel. With audio remixing, you can output more or fewer audio channels than your input audio source provides.
declarations.title: RemixSettings

declarations.comments: Use Respond to AFD (RespondToAfd) to specify how the service changes the video itself in response to AFD values in the input. * Choose Respond to clip the input video frame according to the AFD value, input display aspect ratio, and output display aspect ratio. * Choose Passthrough to include the input AFD values. Do not choose this when AfdSignaling is set to (NONE). A preferred implementation of this workflow is to set RespondToAfd to (NONE) and set AfdSignaling to (AUTO). * Choose None to remove all input AFD values from this output.
declarations.title: RespondToAfd

declarations.comments: Applies only if your input aspect ratio is different from your output aspect ratio. Enable Stretch to output (StretchToOutput) to have the service stretch your video image to fit. Leave this setting disabled to allow the service to letterbox your video instead. This setting overrides any positioning value you specify elsewhere in the job.
declarations.title: ScalingBehavior

declarations.comments: Set Framerate (SccDestinationFramerate) to make sure that the captions and the video are synchronized in the output. Specify a framerate that matches the framerate of the associated video. If the video framerate is 29.97, choose 29.97 dropframe (FRAMERATE_29_97_DROPFRAME) only if the video has video_insertion=true and drop_frame_timecode=true; otherwise, choose 29.97 non-dropframe (FRAMERATE_29_97_NON_DROPFRAME).
declarations.title: SccDestinationFramerate

declarations.comments: Settings for SCC caption output.
declarations.title: SccDestinationSettings

declarations.comments: Settings for use with a SPEKE key provider
declarations.title: SpekeKeyProvider

declarations.comments: Settings for use with a SPEKE key provider.
declarations.title: StaticKeyProvider

declarations.comments: Settings for Teletext caption output
declarations.title: TeletextDestinationSettings

declarations.comments: Settings specific to Teletext caption sources, including Page number.
declarations.title: TeletextSourceSettings

declarations.comments: Timecode burn-in (TimecodeBurnIn)--Burns the output timecode and specified prefix into the output.
declarations.title: TimecodeBurnin

declarations.comments: Use Position (Position) under under Timecode burn-in (TimecodeBurnIn) to specify the location the burned-in timecode on output video.
declarations.title: TimecodeBurninPosition

declarations.comments: Contains settings used to acquire and adjust timecode information from inputs.
declarations.title: TimecodeConfig

declarations.comments: Use Timecode source (TimecodeSource) to set how timecodes are handled within this input. To make sure that your video, audio, captions, and markers are synchronized and that time-based features, such as image inserter, work correctly, choose the Timecode source option that matches your assets. All timecodes are in a 24-hour format with frame number (HH:MM:SS:FF). * Embedded (EMBEDDED) - Use the timecode that is in the input video. If no embedded timecode is in the source, the service will use Start at 0 (ZEROBASED) instead. * Start at 0 (ZEROBASED) - Set the timecode of the initial frame to 00:00:00:00. * Specified Start (SPECIFIEDSTART) - Set the timecode of the initial frame to a value other than zero. You use Start timecode (Start) to provide this value.
declarations.title: TimecodeSource

declarations.comments: If PASSTHROUGH, inserts ID3 timed metadata from the timed_metadata REST command into this output.
declarations.title: TimedMetadata

declarations.comments: Enable Timed metadata insertion (TimedMetadataInsertion) to include ID3 tags in your job. To include timed metadata, you must enable it here, enable it in each output container, and specify tags and timecodes in ID3 insertion (Id3Insertion) objects.
declarations.title: TimedMetadataInsertion

declarations.comments: Information about when jobs are submitted, started, and finished is specified in Unix epoch format in seconds.
declarations.title: Timing

declarations.comments: Too many requests have been sent in too short of a time. The service limits the rate at which it will accept requests.
declarations.title: TooManyRequestsException

declarations.comments: Settings specific to TTML caption outputs, including Pass style information (TtmlStylePassthrough).
declarations.title: TtmlDestinationSettings

declarations.comments: Pass through style and position information from a TTML-like input source (TTML, SMPTE-TT, CFF-TT) to the CFF-TT output or TTML output.
declarations.title: TtmlStylePassthrough

declarations.comments: Type of video codec
declarations.title: VideoCodec

declarations.comments: Video codec settings, (CodecSettings) under (VideoDescription), contains the group of settings related to video encoding. The settings in this group vary depending on the value you choose for Video codec (Codec). For each codec enum you choose, define the corresponding settings object. The following lists the codec enum, settings object pairs. * H_264, H264Settings * H_265, H265Settings * MPEG2, Mpeg2Settings * PRORES, ProresSettings * FRAME_CAPTURE, FrameCaptureSettings
declarations.title: VideoCodecSettings

declarations.comments: Settings for video outputs
declarations.title: VideoDescription

declarations.comments: Contains details about the output's video stream
declarations.title: VideoDetail

declarations.comments: Find additional transcoding features under Preprocessors (VideoPreprocessors). Enable the features at each output individually. These features are disabled by default.
declarations.title: VideoPreprocessor

declarations.comments: Selector for video.
declarations.title: VideoSelector

declarations.comments: Enable Timecode insertion to include timecode information in this output. Do this in the API by setting (VideoTimecodeInsertion) to (PIC_TIMING_SEI). To get timecodes to appear correctly in your output, also set up the timecode configuration for your job in the input settings. Only enable Timecode insertion when the input framerate is identical to output framerate. Disable this setting to remove the timecode from the output. Default is disabled.
declarations.title: VideoTimecodeInsertion

declarations.comments: Required when you set (Codec) under (AudioDescriptions)>(CodecSettings) to the value WAV.
declarations.title: WavSettings
